🔍 TryHackMe TakeOver Writeup

The TakeOver room introduces one of the most interesting web vulnerabilities: Subdomain Takeover.

💡 What is Subdomain Takeover?

Subdomain takeover occurs when a subdomain is pointing to a service that is no longer active or configured properly.

For example:

blog.example.com → points to GitHub Pages
But GitHub repo is deleted ❌

Now an attacker can:

Create a repo with same name
Take control of the subdomain ✅
⚠️ Why This is Dangerous
Attackers can host phishing pages
Can steal user data
Can damage company reputation
🧪 Key Concept Learned
DNS misconfiguration = security risk
Always remove unused services
Monitor subdomains regularly
🧠 Final Thoughts

This room is beginner-friendly but teaches a real-world vulnerability that many companies still face.
